Reasoning: The paper discusses data analysis tasks in high performance computing (HPC) and compares the performance of Message Passing Interface (MPI) and cloud-based applications using Apache Spark. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to distributed computing, data science, and databases. Specifically, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.DB (Databases) are likely sub-categories given the focus on large-scale data analysis and out-of-core methods. Additionally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) could be a relevant sub-category given the use of map-reduce and the comparison of different programming languages. Finally, cs.SC (Supercomputing) is a possible sub-category given the use of large-scale supercomputers in the experiments.
